 High winds blowing sand across the United Arab Emirates have caused mayhem for people trying to travel and work in the country .
Dubai 's large skyscrapers and tower blocks can barely be made out because of the sandstorm has seen visibility drops to less than 500 meters , while walkers have donned masks to protect their lungs .
In Abu Dhabi police say a 24-year-old was airlifted to the hospital after being seriously injured in a traffic accident .